{
  "id": "1pe",
  "name": "First Epistle General of Peter",
  "order": 21,
  "section": "New Testament",
  "folios": [],
  "chapters": [
    {
      "chapter": 1,
      "verses": [
        {
          "verse": 1,
          "sinaiticus": {},
          "text": "Peter, an apostle of Jesus Christ, to the strangers scattered",
          "fragment": false,
          "notes": null,
          "fulltext_links": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translation": "KJV",
              "url": "/full/kjv/1pe/1/1"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "verse": 2,
          "sinaiticus": {},
          "text": "Elect according to the foreknowledge of God the Father, through sanctification of the Spirit, unto obedience and sprinkling of the blood of Jesus Christ: Grace unto you, and peace, be multiplied.",
          "fragment": false,
          "notes": null,
          "fulltext_links": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translation": "KJV",
              "url": "/full/kjv/1pe/1/2"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "verse": 3,
          "sinaiticus": {},
          "text": "Blessed be the God and Father of our Lord Jesus Christ, which according to his abundant mercy hath begotten us again unto a lively",
          "fragment": false,
          "notes": null,
          "fulltext_links": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translation": "KJV",
              "url": "/full/kjv/1pe/1/3"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "verse": 4,
          "sinaiticus": {},
          "text": "To an inheritance incorruptible, and undefiled, and that fadeth not away,",
          "fragment": false,
          "notes": null,
          "fulltext_links": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translation": "KJV",
              "url": "/full/kjv/1pe/1/4"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "verse": 5,
          "sinaiticus": {},
          "text": "Who are kept by the power of God through faith unto salvation ready to be revealed in the last time.",
          "fragment": false,
          "notes": null,
          "fulltext_links": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translation": "KJV",
              "url": "/full/kjv/1pe/1/5"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "verse": 6,
          "sinaiticus": {},
          "text": "Wherein ye greatly rejoice, though now for a season, if need be,",
          "fragment": false,
          "notes": null,
          "fulltext_links": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translation": "KJV",
              "url": "/full/kjv/1pe/1/6"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "verse": 7,
          "sinaiticus": {},
          "text": "That the trial of your faith, being much more precious than of gold that perisheth, though it be tried with fire, might be found unto praise and honour",
          "fragment": false,
          "notes": null,
          "fulltext_links": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translation": "KJV",
              "url": "/full/kjv/1pe/1/7"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "verse": 8,
          "sinaiticus": {},
          "text": "Whom having not seen, ye love; in whom, though now ye see him not, yet believing, ye rejoice",
          "fragment": false,
          "notes": null,
          "fulltext_links": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translation": "KJV",
              "url": "/full/kjv/1pe/1/8"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "verse": 9,
          "sinaiticus": {},
          "text": "Receiving the end of your faith, even the salvation of your souls.",
          "fragment": false,
          "notes": null,
          "fulltext_links": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translation": "KJV",
              "url": "/full/kjv/1pe/1/9"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "verse": 10,
          "sinaiticus": {},
          "text": "Of which salvation the prophets have enquired and searched diligently, who prophesied of the grace that should come unto you:",
          "fragment": false,
          "notes": null,
          "fulltext_links": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translation": "KJV",
              "url": "/full/kjv/1pe/1/10"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "verse": 11,
          "sinaiticus": {},
          "text": "Searching what, or what manner of time the Spirit of Christ which was in them did signify, when it testified beforehand the sufferings of Christ, and the glory that should follow.",
          "fragment": false,
          "notes": null,
          "fulltext_links": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translation": "KJV",
              "url": "/full/kjv/1pe/1/11"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "verse": 12,
          "sinaiticus": {},
          "text": "Unto whom it was revealed, that not unto themselves, but unto us they did minister the things, which are now reported unto you by them that have preached the gospel unto you with the Holy Ghost sent down from heaven; which things the angels desire to look into.",
          "fragment": false,
          "notes": null,
          "fulltext_links": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translation": "KJV",
              "url": "/full/kjv/1pe/1/12"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "verse": 13,
          "sinaiticus": {},
          "text": "Wherefore gird up the loins of your mind, be sober, and hope to the end for the grace that is to be brought unto you at the revelation",
          "fragment": false,
          "notes": null,
          "fulltext_links": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translation": "KJV",
              "url": "/full/kjv/1pe/1/13"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "verse": 14,
          "sinaiticus": {},
          "text": "As obedient children, not fashioning yourselves",
          "fragment": false,
          "notes": null,
          "fulltext_links": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translation": "KJV",
              "url": "/full/kjv/1pe/1/14"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "verse": 15,
          "sinaiticus": {},
          "text": "But as he which hath called you is holy, so be ye holy in all manner of conversation;",
          "fragment": false,
          "notes": null,
          "fulltext_links": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translation": "KJV",
              "url": "/full/kjv/1pe/1/15"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "verse": 16,
          "sinaiticus": {},
          "text": "Because it is written, Be ye holy; for I am holy.",
          "fragment": false,
          "notes": null,
          "fulltext_links": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translation": "KJV",
              "url": "/full/kjv/1pe/1/16"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "verse": 17,
          "sinaiticus": {},
          "text": "And if ye call on the Father, who without respect of persons judgeth according to every manâ€™s work, pass the time of your",
          "fragment": false,
          "notes": null,
          "fulltext_links": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translation": "KJV",
              "url": "/full/kjv/1pe/1/17"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "verse": 18,
          "sinaiticus": {},
          "text": "Forasmuch as ye know that ye were not redeemed with corruptible things, as silver and gold, from your vain",
          "fragment": false,
          "notes": null,
          "fulltext_links": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translation": "KJV",
              "url": "/full/kjv/1pe/1/18"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "verse": 19,
          "sinaiticus": {},
          "text": "But with the precious blood of Christ, as of a lamb without blemish and without",
          "fragment": false,
          "notes": null,
          "fulltext_links": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translation": "KJV",
              "url": "/full/kjv/1pe/1/19"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "verse": 20,
          "sinaiticus": {},
          "text": "Who verily was foreordained before the foundation of the",
          "fragment": false,
          "notes": null,
          "fulltext_links": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translation": "KJV",
              "url": "/full/kjv/1pe/1/20"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "verse": 21,
          "sinaiticus": {},
          "text": "Who by him do believe in God, that raised him up from the dead, and gave him glory; that your faith and hope might be in God.",
          "fragment": false,
          "notes": null,
          "fulltext_links": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translation": "KJV",
              "url": "/full/kjv/1pe/1/21"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "verse": 22,
          "sinaiticus": {},
          "text": "Seeing ye have purified your souls in obeying the truth through the Spirit unto unfeigned love of the brethren, see that ye love one",
          "fragment": false,
          "notes": null,
          "fulltext_links": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translation": "KJV",
              "url": "/full/kjv/1pe/1/22"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "verse": 23,
          "sinaiticus": {},
          "text": "Being born again, not of corruptible seed, but of incorruptible, by the word of God, which liveth and abideth for ever.",
          "fragment": false,
          "notes": null,
          "fulltext_links": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translation": "KJV",
              "url": "/full/kjv/1pe/1/23"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "verse": 24,
          "sinaiticus": {},
          "text": "For all flesh is as grass, and all the glory of man as the flower of grass. The grass withereth, and the flower thereof falleth away:",
          "fragment": false,
          "notes": null,
          "fulltext_links": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translation": "KJV",
              "url": "/full/kjv/1pe/1/24"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "verse": 25,
          "sinaiticus": {},
          "text": "But the word of the Lord endureth for ever. And this is the word which by the gospel is preached unto you.",
          "fragment": false,
          "notes": null,
          "fulltext_links": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translation": "KJV",
              "url": "/full/kjv/1pe/1/25"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "chapter": 2,
      "verses": [
        {
          "verse": 1,
          "sinaiticus": {},
          "text": "Wherefore laying aside all malice, and all guile, and hypocrisies,",
          "fragment": false,
          "notes": null,
          "fulltext_links": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translation": "KJV",
              "url": "/full/kjv/1pe/2/1"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "verse": 2,
          "sinaiticus": {},
          "text": "As newborn babes, desire the",
          "fragment": false,
          "notes": null,
          "fulltext_links": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translation": "KJV",
              "url": "/full/kjv/1pe/2/2"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "verse": 3,
          "sinaiticus": {},
          "text": "If so be ye have tasted that the Lord is gracious.",
          "fragment": false,
          "notes": null,
          "fulltext_links": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translation": "KJV",
              "url": "/full/kjv/1pe/2/3"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "verse": 4,
          "sinaiticus": {},
          "text": "To whom coming, as unto a living stone, disallowed indeed of men,",
          "fragment": false,
          "notes": null,
          "fulltext_links": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translation": "KJV",
              "url": "/full/kjv/1pe/2/4"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "verse": 5,
          "sinaiticus": {},
          "text": "Ye also, as lively stones, are built up a spiritual house, an holy priesthood, to offer up spiritual sacrifices, acceptable to God by Jesus Christ.",
          "fragment": false,
          "notes": null,
          "fulltext_links": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translation": "KJV",
              "url": "/full/kjv/1pe/2/5"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "verse": 6,
          "sinaiticus": {},
          "text": "Wherefore also it is contained in the scripture, Behold, I lay in Sion a chief corner stone, elect, precious: and he that believeth on him shall not be confounded.",
          "fragment": false,
          "notes": null,
          "fulltext_links": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translation": "KJV",
              "url": "/full/kjv/1pe/2/6"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "verse": 7,
          "sinaiticus": {},
          "text": "Unto you therefore which believe he is precious: but unto them which be disobedient, the stone which the builders disallowed, the",
          "fragment": false,
          "notes": null,
          "fulltext_links": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translation": "KJV",
              "url": "/full/kjv/1pe/2/7"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "verse": 8,
          "sinaiticus": {},
          "text": "And a stone of stumbling, and a rock of offence, even to them which stumble at the word, being disobedient: whereunto also they were appointed.",
          "fragment": false,
          "notes": null,
          "fulltext_links": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translation": "KJV",
              "url": "/full/kjv/1pe/2/8"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "verse": 9,
          "sinaiticus": {},
          "text": "But ye are a chosen generation, a royal priesthood, an holy nation, a peculiar people; that ye should shew forth the praises of him who hath called you out of darkness into his marvellous light;",
          "fragment": false,
          "notes": null,
          "fulltext_links": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translation": "KJV",
              "url": "/full/kjv/1pe/2/9"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "verse": 10,
          "sinaiticus": {},
          "text": "Which in time past were not a people, but are now the people of God: which had not obtained mercy, but now have obtained mercy.",
          "fragment": false,
          "notes": null,
          "fulltext_links": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translation": "KJV",
              "url": "/full/kjv/1pe/2/10"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "verse": 11,
          "sinaiticus": {},
          "text": "Dearly beloved, I beseech you as strangers and pilgrims, abstain",
          "fragment": false,
          "notes": null,
          "fulltext_links": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translation": "KJV",
              "url": "/full/kjv/1pe/2/11"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "verse": 12,
          "sinaiticus": {},
          "text": "Having your conversation honest among the Gentiles: that, whereas they speak against you as evildoers, they may by your good works, which they shall behold, glorify God in the day of visitation.",
          "fragment": false,
          "notes": null,
          "fulltext_links": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translation": "KJV",
              "url": "/full/kjv/1pe/2/12"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "verse": 13,
          "sinaiticus": {},
          "text": "Submit yourselves to every ordinance of man for the Lordâ€™s sake:",
          "fragment": false,
          "notes": null,
          "fulltext_links": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translation": "KJV",
              "url": "/full/kjv/1pe/2/13"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "verse": 14,
          "sinaiticus": {},
          "text": "Or unto governors, as unto them that are sent by him for the punishment of evildoers, and for the praise of them that do well.",
          "fragment": false,
          "notes": null,
          "fulltext_links": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translation": "KJV",
              "url": "/full/kjv/1pe/2/14"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "verse": 15,
          "sinaiticus": {},
          "text": "For so is the will of God, that with well doing ye may put to",
          "fragment": false,
          "notes": null,
          "fulltext_links": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translation": "KJV",
              "url": "/full/kjv/1pe/2/15"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "verse": 16,
          "sinaiticus": {},
          "text": "As free, and not using your liberty for a cloke of maliciousness, but as the servants of God.",
          "fragment": false,
          "notes": null,
          "fulltext_links": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translation": "KJV",
              "url": "/full/kjv/1pe/2/16"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "verse": 17,
          "sinaiticus": {},
          "text": "Honour all men. Love the brotherhood. Fear God. Honour the king.",
          "fragment": false,
          "notes": null,
          "fulltext_links": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translation": "KJV",
              "url": "/full/kjv/1pe/2/17"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "verse": 18,
          "sinaiticus": {},
          "text": "Servants, be subject to your masters with all fear; not only to the good and gentle, but also to the froward.",
          "fragment": false,
          "notes": null,
          "fulltext_links": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translation": "KJV",
              "url": "/full/kjv/1pe/2/18"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "verse": 19,
          "sinaiticus": {},
          "text": "For this is thankworthy, if a man for conscience toward God endure grief, suffering wrongfully.",
          "fragment": false,
          "notes": null,
          "fulltext_links": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translation": "KJV",
              "url": "/full/kjv/1pe/2/19"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "verse": 20,
          "sinaiticus": {},
          "text": "For what glory is it, if, when ye be buffeted for your faults, ye shall take it patiently? but if, when ye do well, and suffer for it, ye take it patiently, this is acceptable with God.",
          "fragment": false,
          "notes": null,
          "fulltext_links": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translation": "KJV",
              "url": "/full/kjv/1pe/2/20"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "verse": 21,
          "sinaiticus": {},
          "text": "For even hereunto were ye called: because Christ also suffered",
          "fragment": false,
          "notes": null,
          "fulltext_links": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translation": "KJV",
              "url": "/full/kjv/1pe/2/21"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "verse": 22,
          "sinaiticus": {},
          "text": "",
          "fragment": false,
          "notes": null,
          "fulltext_links": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translation": "KJV",
              "url": "/full/kjv/1pe/2/22"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "verse": 23,
          "sinaiticus": {},
          "text": "Who, when he was reviled, reviled not again; when he suffered, he threatened",
          "fragment": false,
          "notes": null,
          "fulltext_links": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translation": "KJV",
              "url": "/full/kjv/1pe/2/23"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "verse": 24,
          "sinaiticus": {},
          "text": "Who his own self bare our sins in his own body on the tree, that we, being dead to sins, should live unto righteousness: by whose stripes ye were healed.",
          "fragment": false,
          "notes": null,
          "fulltext_links": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translation": "KJV",
              "url": "/full/kjv/1pe/2/24"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "verse": 25,
          "sinaiticus": {},
          "text": "For ye were as sheep going astray; but are now returned unto the Shepherd and Bishop of your souls.",
          "fragment": false,
          "notes": null,
          "fulltext_links": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translation": "KJV",
              "url": "/full/kjv/1pe/2/25"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "chapter": 3,
      "verses": [
        {
          "verse": 1,
          "sinaiticus": {},
          "text": "Likewise, ye wives, be in subjection to your own husbands; that, if any obey not the word, they also may without the word be won by the",
          "fragment": false,
          "notes": null,
          "fulltext_links": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translation": "KJV",
              "url": "/full/kjv/1pe/3/1"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "verse": 2,
          "sinaiticus": {},
          "text": "While they behold your chaste conversation coupled with fear.",
          "fragment": false,
          "notes": null,
          "fulltext_links": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translation": "KJV",
              "url": "/full/kjv/1pe/3/2"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "verse": 3,
          "sinaiticus": {},
          "text": "Whose adorning let it not be that outward adorning of plaiting the",
          "fragment": false,
          "notes": null,
          "fulltext_links": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translation": "KJV",
              "url": "/full/kjv/1pe/3/3"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "verse": 4,
          "sinaiticus": {},
          "text": "But let it be the hidden man of the heart, in that which is not corruptible, even the ornament of a meek and quiet spirit, which is in the sight of God of great price.",
          "fragment": false,
          "notes": null,
          "fulltext_links": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translation": "KJV",
              "url": "/full/kjv/1pe/3/4"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "verse": 5,
          "sinaiticus": {},
          "text": "For after this manner in the old time the holy women also, who trusted in God, adorned themselves, being in subjection unto their own",
          "fragment": false,
          "notes": null,
          "fulltext_links": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translation": "KJV",
              "url": "/full/kjv/1pe/3/5"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "verse": 6,
          "sinaiticus": {},
          "text": "Even as Sara obeyed Abraham, calling him lord: whose daughters ye are, as long as ye do well, and are not afraid with any amazement.",
          "fragment": false,
          "notes": null,
          "fulltext_links": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translation": "KJV",
              "url": "/full/kjv/1pe/3/6"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "verse": 7,
          "sinaiticus": {},
          "text": "Likewise, ye husbands, dwell with them according to knowledge, giving honour unto the wife, as unto the weaker vessel, and as being heirs together of the grace of life; that your prayers be not hindered.",
          "fragment": false,
          "notes": null,
          "fulltext_links": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translation": "KJV",
              "url": "/full/kjv/1pe/3/7"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "verse": 8,
          "sinaiticus": {},
          "text": "Finally, be ye all of one mind, having compassion one of another,",
          "fragment": false,
          "notes": null,
          "fulltext_links": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translation": "KJV",
              "url": "/full/kjv/1pe/3/8"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "verse": 9,
          "sinaiticus": {},
          "text": "Not rendering evil for evil, or railing for railing: but contrariwise blessing; knowing that ye are thereunto called, that ye should inherit a blessing.",
          "fragment": false,
          "notes": null,
          "fulltext_links": [
            {
              "lang": "en",
              "translation": "KJV",
              "url": "/full/kjv/1pe/3/9"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "verse": 10,
          "sinaiticus": {},
